      <section class="detail-block">
        <h2>Application Scenarios</h2>
        <div class="scenario-list">
          <div class="scenario-item">
            <h3>Large-Format Display Film Manufacturing</h3>
            <p>Optical films for large displays — 32-inch, 55-inch, and larger — present a serious cleaning challenge because conventional cleaning equipment cannot cover the full film width in a single pass without seaming artifacts. The STFK series is available in widths from 338mm to 948mm, with each model providing full-width cleaning that eliminates the need for multi-pass cleaning and the seam defects it causes.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="scenario-item">
            <h3>Diffuser, Prism, and Polarizer Film Preparation</h3>
            <p>Optical films including diffuser sheets, brightness enhancement films (BEF), and polarizers must be free of particles before lamination into a display module. A single particle trapped between film layers creates a visible hotspot or dark spot defect in the finished display. The STFK Series removes particles across the full film width before the lamination stage, protecting display quality from the film manufacturing side.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="scenario-item">
            <h3>Optical Coating Pre-Treatment</h3>
            <p>Anti-reflection, anti-glare, and hard-coat optical films require a perfectly clean substrate surface before the coating process. Surface particles cause coating voids and adhesion failures that reduce the effectiveness of the coating and create visible defects. The STFK Series provides the particle-free surface baseline required for consistent, high-yield optical coating processes.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="detail-block">
        <h2>Choosing the Right STFK Model Width</h2>
        <p>The STFK series is available in four cleaning widths: 338mm, 448mm, 738mm, and 948mm. Select the model whose cleaning width equals or exceeds your maximum film width. Using a model narrower than your film requires multiple passes, which risks alignment errors and seam artifacts. Contact us if your film width falls between standard model sizes — custom widths are available on request. For polarizer film applications requiring precision grade cleaning, see our dedicated <a href="/products/cleaning-machine/polarizer-cleaner">Polarizer Precision Cleaning Machine</a>.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="detail-block faq-block">
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <div class="faq-list">
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">What film types can the STFK Series clean?</h3>
            <p class="faq-answer">The STFK Series handles optical films including diffuser sheets, prism sheets (BEF), polarizer films, TAC films, protective films, and other optical substrates used in LCD and display manufacturing. The adhesive roller cleaning method is safe for all standard optical film surfaces.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">What cleaning widths are available?</h3>
            <p class="faq-answer">The STFK Series is available in four standard widths: 338mm, 448mm, 738mm, and 948mm. Custom widths are available on request for non-standard film dimensions.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">Does the cleaning process damage optical film coatings?</h3>
            <p class="faq-answer">No. The adhesive roller cleaning method lifts particles from the film surface through gentle controlled contact without abrasives, solvents, or UV exposure. The magnetic levitation drive ensures smooth, vibration-free transport that does not stress coated film surfaces.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">Can the machine handle very thin optical films?</h3>
            <p class="faq-answer">Yes. The transport and cleaning pressure systems are designed for thin, flexible optical film materials. The magnetic levitation drive eliminates vibration that could cause thin films to wrinkle or deform during cleaning.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">Does the STFK Series include static elimination?</h3>
            <p class="faq-answer">Yes. Integrated intelligent static elimination is included, neutralizing electrostatic charge on film surfaces simultaneously with particle removal. This is essential for optical films, which are highly susceptible to electrostatic particle re-attraction.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">What is the difference between the optical film cleaner and the polarizer cleaner?</h3>
            <p class="faq-answer">The STFK optical film cleaner is optimized for large-format film cleaning across widths up to 948mm. The polarizer precision cleaner (ST-F7x40 series) is configured specifically for polarizer film dimensions and pre-lamination precision cleaning. If you clean both film types, they are typically handled by separate dedicated machines for each process stage.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

